02:21.200 --> 02:22.590
♪ TAKE FLIGHT ♪

02:22.600 --> 02:28.990
♪♪

02:29.000 --> 02:35.390
♪♪

02:35.400 --> 02:37.330
Blue:
AUNTIE NOVA'S HERE!

02:39.530 --> 02:40.860
WHERE YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

02:40.860 --> 02:42.530
A-AUNTIE NOVA'S OUTSIDE.

02:42.530 --> 02:44.990
I KNOW SHE OUTSIDE.

02:45.000 --> 02:47.260
BUT SHE'S SICK, AND I DON'T
NEED YOU GETTING SICK, TOO.

02:47.260 --> 02:48.530
SO WHAT I NEED YOU
TO DO IS GRAB

02:48.530 --> 02:50.460
ALL YOUR SMALL CLOTHES
OUT THIS DRESSER

02:50.460 --> 02:52.060
AND PUT 'EM
IN THE GIVEAWAY BAG.

02:52.060 --> 02:55.530
BUT I HAVEN'T SEEN
AUNTIE NOVA IN FOREVER.

02:55.530 --> 02:57.390
I JUST WANTED TO SAY HI.

02:57.400 --> 02:59.290
COME ON.
DO WHAT I SAID.

03:06.060 --> 03:07.330
DOIN', AUNT NOVA?

03:07.330 --> 03:10.860
HEARD YOU'RE HANDING OUT
SECOND CHANCES.

03:10.860 --> 03:12.530
THOUGHT I'D TRY MY LUCK.

03:16.260 --> 03:19.090
GONNA STAY MAD AT ME
FOREVER, RALPH ANGEL?

03:19.100 --> 03:22.360
-I'LL TRY.
-WELL, CAN YOU TRY AND TALK?

03:22.360 --> 03:23.830
THERE'S SOME THINGS
I NEED TO TELL YOU.

03:23.830 --> 03:26.060
YOU GOT SOME MORE BOMBS
TO DROP ON ME?

03:26.060 --> 03:28.130
OR WHITE FOLK
YOU WANNA BUY INTO

03:28.130 --> 03:31.060
THE, UH, LANDRY-BORDELON
FAMILY REUNION?

03:31.060 --> 03:32.530
YEAH, I HEARD
THAT CAME FROM YOU.

03:32.530 --> 03:34.530
I TOLD CHARLEY THE TRUTH
ABOUT OUR FAMILY TREE

03:34.530 --> 03:36.390
AFTER I WORKED THINGS OUT
BETWEEN US.

03:36.400 --> 03:37.660
NOW I'M HERE.

03:37.660 --> 03:41.430
ME AND AUNT VI
NEXT ON YOUR LIST?

03:41.430 --> 03:43.360
YOU KNOW WE GOT BLUE
IN THERAPY NOW?

03:43.360 --> 03:45.030
-WAIT. WHY?
-WHY?

03:45.030 --> 03:49.360
'CAUSE HE FOUND OUT I WASN'T HIS
DADDY FROM SOME KID AT SCHOOL!

03:49.360 --> 03:51.690
YOU SAID THAT WASN'T
GONNA HAPPEN.

03:51.700 --> 03:53.490
WELL, IT DID.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.390
I'M SORRY, RA.

03:55.400 --> 03:58.460
THREW DARLA'S PAST
RIGHT UP IN HER FACE.

03:58.460 --> 04:01.660
HER HEAD ALL MESSED UP.

04:01.660 --> 04:04.330
SHE'D HAVE BEEN
THREE YEARS SOBER.

04:04.330 --> 04:06.860
NOW SHE GOTTA START
ALL OVER.

04:06.860 --> 04:09.190
DARLA RELAPSED?

04:09.200 --> 04:11.260
I REALIZED SOMETHING.

04:11.260 --> 04:14.860
I AIN'T GOTTA WORRY ABOUT
THE LANDRYS BRINGING US DOWN.

04:14.860 --> 04:17.730
WHY I GOTTA WORRY ABOUT ENEMIES?
FOR WHAT?

04:17.730 --> 04:21.130
WHEN I GOT A SISTER LIKE
NOVA BORDELON RIGHT HERE.

04:21.130 --> 04:22.930
[ SCOFFS ]

04:22.930 --> 04:30.930
♪♪

04:30.930 --> 04:32.860
[ SIGHS ]

04:32.860 --> 04:35.460
♪♪

04:35.460 --> 04:37.330
MA, YOU KNOW YOU'RE
BEING A LITTLE EXTRA

04:37.330 --> 04:38.590
WITH ALL OF THIS, RIGHT?

04:38.600 --> 04:40.790
YOU GOT AN ELECTION NEXT WEEK.
MAYBE YOU SHOULD JUST --

04:40.800 --> 04:42.930
UH, EXCUSE ME.

04:42.930 --> 04:46.930
YOU ARE GOING
TO HARVARD.

04:46.930 --> 04:48.930
WE ARE GOING TO
CELEBRATE YOU TOMORROW,

04:48.930 --> 04:51.860
WHETHER YOU WANT TO
OR NOT.

04:51.860 --> 04:54.930
[ CHUCKLES ]
AND NICE SWEATSHIRT.

04:54.930 --> 04:56.790
WELL, I THOUGHT I NEEDED
SOMETHING TO WEAR

04:56.800 --> 05:00.330
WHEN I FLY UP FOR
THE HARVARD-YALE GAME.

05:00.330 --> 05:03.160
SO THAT'S A THING I CAN
LOOK FORWARD TO, AS WELL?

05:03.160 --> 05:05.930
GREAT.

05:05.930 --> 05:10.860
MICAH. YOU HAVE TO
CELEBRATE YOUR WINS.

05:10.860 --> 05:13.790
AFTER EVERYTHING
YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH --

05:13.800 --> 05:16.330
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH --
WE DESERVE A VICTORY LAP.

05:16.330 --> 05:18.930
RIGHT? COME ON.

05:18.930 --> 05:22.390
LET ME PROUD
OF MY BABY!

05:22.400 --> 05:24.590
-ALRIGHT. ALRIGHT.
-MY BABY!

05:24.600 --> 05:26.730
[ LAUGHS ]

05:26.730 --> 05:30.190
I'M GONNA GET AN EXTRA HELIUM
CANISTER OUT OF THE GARAGE.

05:30.200 --> 05:32.390
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:39.160 --> 05:40.690
HUH.

05:46.660 --> 05:48.730
[ CELLPHONE CLICKING ]

05:50.260 --> 05:53.330
[ Line ringing ]

05:53.330 --> 05:56.590
<i> -New Orleans Daily News.</i>
-HEY, IT'S NOVA.

05:56.600 --> 05:59.690
CAN YOU DO A DEEP DIVE
INTO A NAME FOR ME?

05:59.700 --> 06:00.890
Yeah, sure.

06:00.900 --> 06:04.630
PARKER CAMPBELL.
CONNECTED TO OLD WORLD ENERGY.

06:04.630 --> 06:06.390
Campbell.
I'll look him up.

06:06.400 --> 06:09.930
YEAH.
HE'S A BIT OF A GHOST.

06:09.930 --> 06:11.790
Let me see
what I can find on him.

06:11.800 --> 06:14.060
THANKS.

06:14.060 --> 06:15.630
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

06:15.630 --> 06:22.490
♪♪

06:26.530 --> 06:28.990
AUNT VI. HI.

06:29.000 --> 06:31.290
WELL, COME -- COME IN.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.590
I NEED
JIMMY DALE'S ADDRESS.

06:36.600 --> 06:39.130
WHY?

06:39.130 --> 06:42.590
NOT THAT IT IS ANY OF
YOUR BUSINESS, NOVA,

06:42.600 --> 06:44.530
BUT I NEED
TO RETURN SOMETHING.

06:44.530 --> 06:46.860
I-I DON'T KNOW
WHERE TO SEND IT.

06:46.860 --> 06:49.260
YOU TALK TO HIM
ABOUT YOUR BOOK, SO --

06:49.260 --> 06:52.530
THIS IS HARD.

06:52.530 --> 06:57.790
FOR MONTHS, I'VE WANTED TO
SEE YOU, TALK TO YOU, HUG YOU.

06:57.800 --> 06:59.660
AND HERE YOU ARE.

06:59.660 --> 07:01.860
BUT I DON'T THINK
YOU'RE TELLING ME THE TRUTH.

07:01.860 --> 07:04.190
I DON'T CARE
WHAT YOU THINK, NOVA.

07:04.200 --> 07:08.660
PLEASE TELL ME YOU'RE NOT
PLANNING ON CONFRONTING HIM...

07:08.660 --> 07:11.530
IN PERSON, ALONE.

07:11.530 --> 07:15.060
♪♪

07:15.060 --> 07:19.190
YOU'RE RESPONSIBLE FOR
UNLEASHING THIS DEMON.

07:19.200 --> 07:22.990
THE LEAST YOU CAN DO
IS HELP ME GET RID OF IT.

07:26.930 --> 07:30.190
I KNOW THAT NOW.

07:30.200 --> 07:31.860
AND YOU'RE RIGHT.

07:31.860 --> 07:35.660
SO I WILL GIVE YOU
HIS ADDRESS...

07:35.660 --> 07:40.160
ONLY IF I DRIVE YOU
AND YOU TALK TO ME.

07:40.160 --> 07:45.390
♪♪

07:45.400 --> 07:47.660
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

07:49.600 --> 07:52.660
YOU CAN DRIVE.

07:52.660 --> 07:57.590
BUT, NOVA, I WILL TALK TO YOU
WHEN AND IF I'M READY.

07:57.600 --> 08:00.530
♪♪

08:00.530 --> 08:02.460
UNDERSTOOD?

08:02.460 --> 08:05.960
♪♪

08:05.960 --> 08:09.930
<i> I EMBRACE THE DIVERSITY</i>
<i> OF MY HERITAGE.</i>

08:09.930 --> 08:12.060
<i> MY GOAL IS TO EDUCATE MYSELF</i>

08:12.060 --> 08:14.930
<i> ON THE HISTORIES</i>
<i> BETWEEN OUR COMMUNITIES</i>

08:14.930 --> 08:17.560
<i> AND USE THAT KNOWLEDGE</i>
<i> TO BE AN ALLY</i>

08:17.560 --> 08:20.890
<i> AND SUPPORT REAL CHANGE</i>
<i> IN SAINT JO.</i>

08:20.900 --> 08:22.860
Man:<i> MANY VOTERS SAY</i>
<i> THEY DOUBT THE VERACITY</i>

08:22.860 --> 08:25.060
<i> AND TIMING OF THIS EMBRACE.</i>

08:25.060 --> 08:26.930
<i> POLLS SHOW MR. BOUDREAUX</i>
<i> LOSING SOME GROUND,</i>

08:26.930 --> 08:30.590
<i> WITH THE NUMBER OF UNDECIDED</i>
<i> VOTERS RISING SHARPLY.</i>

08:30.600 --> 08:33.130
[ CLICK ]

08:33.130 --> 08:34.760
UH...

08:37.600 --> 08:41.730
I DON'T WANNA PUT A SHADOW
ON THE GOOD NEWS.

08:41.730 --> 08:43.860
WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:43.860 --> 08:45.990
WENT DOWN TO THE PARISH
THIS MORNING,

08:46.000 --> 08:50.330
AND I CHECKED
ON MY REGISTRATION.

08:50.330 --> 08:53.190
TOLD ME I COULDN'T VOTE
'CAUSE I WASN'T A RESIDENT.

08:53.200 --> 08:56.960
MR. PROSPER, YOU'VE LIVED
IN THIS PARISH FOR DECADES.

08:56.960 --> 08:59.960
I ASKED AROUND AT THE FARMERS'
COLLECTIVE THIS MORNING,

08:59.960 --> 09:03.030
AND A WHOLE BUNCH OF FOLKS
ARE HAVING THE SAME PROBLEM.

09:05.660 --> 09:07.060
I WROTE DOWN
THE NAMES.

09:07.060 --> 09:10.190
FOLKS THAT HAVE LIVED HERE
THEIR WHOLE LIFE...

09:10.200 --> 09:14.790
SUDDENLY KICKED OFF
THE ROLLS.

09:14.800 --> 09:17.990
THIS IS NO
INNOCENT MISTAKE.

09:18.000 --> 09:19.860
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:22.060 --> 09:24.460
COME IN, WHY DON'T YOU?

09:24.460 --> 09:26.790
-I WON'T BE HERE LONG.
-GOOD.

09:26.800 --> 09:28.930
PRIVACY, PLEASE, PROSPER?

09:30.800 --> 09:35.190
IT'S OKAY.
THIS WON'T TAKE LONG.

09:35.200 --> 09:39.590
♪♪

09:39.600 --> 09:42.860
WHAT DID YOU DO
TO MY SON?

09:42.860 --> 09:45.060
JACOB?

09:45.060 --> 09:48.690
WHY, COUSIN FRANCES,
WHATEVER DO YOU MEAN?

09:48.700 --> 09:52.830
TELLING HIM THAT MY GRANDMOTHER
IS A BORDELON

09:52.830 --> 09:54.760
OFF THE WORDS FROM SOME

09:54.760 --> 09:57.690
BACK-OF-A-MATCHBOOK
GENEALOGIST?

09:57.700 --> 09:59.690
HAVE YOU LOST YOUR MIND?!

09:59.700 --> 10:00.990
SORRY TO OFFEND YOUR

10:01.000 --> 10:03.730
DAUGHTERS OF THE CONFEDERACY
SENSIBILITIES,

10:03.730 --> 10:06.190
BUT I ONLY SHOOK
THE FAMILY TREE.

10:06.200 --> 10:09.460
I'M NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR WHO FALLS OUT OF IT.

10:09.460 --> 10:13.330
I SIMPLY PROVIDED JACOB
WITH THE TRUTH.

10:13.330 --> 10:14.990
YOU SET HIM UP ON THIS
SOMEHOW.

10:15.000 --> 10:17.960
JACOB IS A GROWN MAN,
AND HE DOESN'T NEED HIS MAMA

10:17.960 --> 10:21.560
RUNNING AFTER HIM
TRYING TO CLEAN UP HIS MESS.

10:21.560 --> 10:25.660
HIS WEAKNESS FOR YOU --

10:25.660 --> 10:27.790
I'LL NEVER UNDERSTAND IT.

10:29.530 --> 10:32.190
BUT YOU DO HAVE CONFIDENCE.

10:32.200 --> 10:35.060
I'LL GIVE YOU THAT.

10:35.060 --> 10:40.190
AS LONG AS YOU REMEMBER,
PRIDE GOETH BEFORE THE FALL.

10:41.360 --> 10:43.960
Prosper:
UH, CHARLEY?

10:43.960 --> 10:45.690
THESE DEPUTIES SAY
THEY WANNA ASK YOU

10:45.700 --> 10:49.860
SOME QUESTIONS ABOUT
THE QUEEN SUGAR FIRE.

10:49.860 --> 10:53.190
LOOKS LIKE YOU'RE BUSY
ALL OF A SUDDEN.

10:53.200 --> 10:55.330
I'LL BE ON MY WAY.

10:55.330 --> 11:02.060
♪♪

11:06.600 --> 11:08.390
I'M GLAD YOU'RE HERE.
I'VE CALLED YOUR OFFICE

11:08.400 --> 11:10.330
SEVERAL TIMES FOR AN UPDATE
ON THE INVESTIGATION.

11:10.330 --> 11:12.330
YES, WE'RE WRAPPING UP
OUR INQUIRY.

11:12.330 --> 11:14.990
WE JUST HAVE
A FEW MORE I's TO DOT,

11:15.000 --> 11:17.030
T's TO CROSS,
BEFORE WE'RE FINISHED.

11:17.030 --> 11:18.960
HE DISCOVERED
IN OUR INVESTIGATION

11:18.960 --> 11:23.230
THE PROBABLE SOURCE OF THE BLAZE
WAS A PROPANE DRIP TORCH.

11:23.230 --> 11:25.460
DID YOU KEEP ONE OF THOSE
AT THE MILL?

11:25.460 --> 11:27.060
NO, NOT THAT I'M AWARE OF.

11:27.060 --> 11:29.160
IT'S THE KIND THAT THEY USE
ON SUGARCANE FARMS

11:29.160 --> 11:30.990
FOR CONTROLLED BURNS.

11:31.000 --> 11:33.560
YOUR BROTHER OWNS
A CANE FARM, RIGHT?

11:36.200 --> 11:37.860
YOU KNOW HE DOES.

11:37.860 --> 11:40.290
WE UNDERSTAND THAT YOU'VE
SPENT SIGNIFICANTLY

11:40.300 --> 11:42.890
ON UPGRADES
AND MAINTENANCE.

11:42.900 --> 11:45.930
WOULD YOU SAY THAT QUEEN SUGAR
WAS EXPENSIVE TO OPERATE?

11:45.930 --> 11:48.330
NO MORE THAN ANY OTHER
STARTUP IN MY INDUSTRY,

11:48.330 --> 11:50.260
ESPECIALLY DURING
THE FIRST TWO YEARS.

11:50.260 --> 11:52.060
IT'S A BIG
FINANCIAL BURDEN --

11:52.060 --> 11:55.590
MAYBE LARGER
THAN YOU ANTICIPATED?

11:55.600 --> 11:57.330
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW
WHERE THIS IS HEADED.

11:57.330 --> 12:02.060
BUT, ONE, I'M WEALTHY,
SO I'M GOOD.

12:02.060 --> 12:05.590
TWO, I WOULDN'T HAVE FOUGHT
TO REGAIN OWNERSHIP OF MY MILL

12:05.600 --> 12:08.990
FROM THE LANDRYS
IF I WAS WORRIED ABOUT MONEY.

12:09.000 --> 12:12.760
DID YOU EVER CHECK INTO FRANCES
BOUDREAUX'S ROLE IN ALL THIS?

12:12.760 --> 12:15.390
WE HAVE NO EVIDENCE
OF HER INVOLVEMENT.

12:15.400 --> 12:18.390
YOUR SON, MICAH,
HOWEVER --

12:18.400 --> 12:20.030
HE WAS INVESTIGATED
FOR POSSIBLE INVOLVEMENT

12:20.030 --> 12:22.360
IN AN ARSON LAST YEAR.
WASN'T HE?

12:22.360 --> 12:24.160
OKAY. WE'RE DONE HERE.

12:24.160 --> 12:27.260
WE CAN CONTINUE FURTHER
WHEN MY ATTORNEY IS PRESENT.

12:27.260 --> 12:29.530
UNTIL THEN, YOU MAY LEAVE.

12:29.530 --> 12:36.130
♪♪

12:36.130 --> 12:42.660
♪♪

12:42.660 --> 12:46.130
-YOU TOLD THE WRONG STORY.
-AUNT VI, I --

12:46.130 --> 12:48.360
YOU TOLD THE WORLD
I WAS BROKEN.

12:48.360 --> 12:51.960
NO! AUNT VI, I TOLD THE WORLD
ABOUT YOUR BREAKTHROUGH.

12:51.960 --> 12:54.930
YOU KNOW HOW TO TALK.
WE KNOW THAT, NOVA.

12:54.930 --> 12:56.860
BUT CAN YOU LISTEN?

12:56.860 --> 13:00.330
CAN YOU ACCEPT YOU TOLD
THE WRONG STORY?

13:00.330 --> 13:01.830
I COUNTED.

13:01.830 --> 13:05.230
YOU WROTE WAY MORE PAGES ON
MY TRIALS THAN ON MY TRIUMPH.

13:05.230 --> 13:07.660
AND I TRIUMPHED,
DAMN IT!

13:07.660 --> 13:13.190
I SHOWED YOU. BY MOVING ON.
BY LIVING MY BEST LIFE.

13:13.200 --> 13:14.930
BY LETTING LOVE
INTO MY LIFE AGAIN

13:14.930 --> 13:17.660
WHEN I COULD'VE SHUT
MY HEART DOWN FOREVER.

13:17.660 --> 13:20.790
♪♪

13:20.800 --> 13:22.930
I SHOWED YOU.

13:22.930 --> 13:29.090
♪♪

13:29.100 --> 13:30.960
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

13:30.960 --> 13:33.490
NO. COME ON.
YOU GOT IT. OHH!

13:33.500 --> 13:35.260
MY AIMING
IS REALLY TERRIBLE.

13:35.260 --> 13:38.990
I'M A LITTLE RUSTY...

13:39.000 --> 13:40.930
[ LAUGHTER ]

13:44.500 --> 13:46.630
[ DOOR OPENS ]

13:48.030 --> 13:50.090
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:51.660 --> 13:52.990
GOOD, AIN'T IT?

13:53.000 --> 13:55.260
MM-HMM.

13:55.260 --> 13:59.690
OUR SON IS, UH,
SUCH A REJUVENATION.

13:59.700 --> 14:01.860
I FEEL STRONGER
JUST BEING NEAR HIM.

14:01.860 --> 14:04.760
HE'S GOOD FOR YOU.

14:04.760 --> 14:07.830
THANK YOU FOR
BELIEVING IN ME...

14:07.830 --> 14:11.360
FOR STANDING BY ME.

14:11.360 --> 14:13.830
WE ALL GOOD FOR
EACH OTHER, REALLY.

14:16.260 --> 14:18.130
-CAN I SHOW YOU SOMETHING?
-MM-HMM.

14:18.130 --> 14:20.960
ALRIGHT.
BE RIGHT BACK.

14:25.700 --> 14:28.960
-HERE YOU GO. KINDA BIG.
-FOR ME?

14:28.960 --> 14:31.230
FOUND IT BACK IN THE CLOSET.
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:31.230 --> 14:32.490
TA-DA.

14:32.500 --> 14:34.130
[ GASPS ]

14:34.130 --> 14:36.460
DID YOU SHOW THIS
TO BLUE?

14:36.460 --> 14:38.390
I'M-A HOLD OFF.

14:38.400 --> 14:42.130
I DON'T WANNA GET HIM UPSET OR
ANYTHING, YOU KNOW, ABOUT POPS.

14:42.130 --> 14:44.130
-HMM.
-HE GOT MAD AT ME

14:44.130 --> 14:46.990
'CAUSE I AIN'T LET HIM
SEE NOVA THIS MORNING.

14:49.460 --> 14:51.430
SHE CAME BY?

14:51.430 --> 14:53.590
[ SCOFFS ]

14:53.600 --> 14:54.990
WHAT FOR?

14:55.000 --> 14:57.990
SAID SHE HAD SOMETHING
IMPORTANT TO TELL ME.

14:58.000 --> 15:00.660
IT'S ALL IMPORTANT
TO NOVA, THOUGH.

15:00.660 --> 15:03.790
I TOLD HER TO JUST GO ON
AND GET 'BOUT HER WAY.

15:03.800 --> 15:05.730
WITHOUT TALKING
TO BLUE?

15:08.660 --> 15:13.390
SO, UM, WHAT'S GONNA
HAPPEN NEXT TIME?

15:13.400 --> 15:15.260
WHAT YOU MEAN?

15:15.260 --> 15:18.790
I MEAN, ARE YOU
JUST GONNA IGNORE HER

15:18.800 --> 15:24.530
AT EVERY SINGLE FAMILY
GATHERING FOREVER?

15:26.900 --> 15:29.630
I AIN'T THINK THAT FAR.

15:29.630 --> 15:33.090
I'M ANGRY AT HER, TOO,
BUT, UH...

15:33.100 --> 15:36.460
BLUE'S NOT GONNA
UNDERSTAND.

15:36.460 --> 15:38.460
YOU AIN'T SAYING SHE
AIN'T DID WRONG BY US.

15:38.460 --> 15:40.330
NO.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.390
BUT...

15:42.400 --> 15:45.730
DESPITE HOW I FEEL
ABOUT HER...

15:45.730 --> 15:48.590
♪♪

15:48.600 --> 15:50.930
...I KNOW
THAT SHE LOVES BLUE.

15:52.460 --> 15:56.260
AND I NEED THAT LITTLE BOY
TO BE SURROUNDED

15:56.260 --> 15:59.930
BY AS MUCH LOVE
AS POSSIBLE.

15:59.930 --> 16:02.460
♪♪

16:02.460 --> 16:05.360
HE'S GONNA NEED IT
ONE DAY.

16:05.360 --> 16:07.660
♪♪

16:07.660 --> 16:11.190
THAT'S REAL BIG OF YOU,
DARLA, BUT...

16:11.200 --> 16:13.660
I AIN'T THERE YET
WITH NOVA.

16:13.660 --> 16:18.060
♪♪

16:18.060 --> 16:21.460
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.
IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

16:24.030 --> 16:26.160
YES, I DO.

16:30.430 --> 16:32.490
STAY HERE.

16:32.500 --> 16:40.560
♪♪

16:40.560 --> 16:48.660
♪♪

16:48.660 --> 16:56.860
♪♪

16:56.860 --> 16:58.790
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

16:58.800 --> 17:08.490
♪♪

17:08.500 --> 17:18.130
♪♪

17:18.130 --> 17:20.260
I KNEW YOU'D BE BACK.

17:25.560 --> 17:30.960
♪♪

17:30.960 --> 17:34.830
THIS BELONGED TO YOU,
NOT ME.

17:34.830 --> 17:40.130
♪♪

17:40.130 --> 17:42.660
AM I SUPPOSED TO
FEEL SOMETHING?

17:42.660 --> 17:47.930
♪♪

17:47.930 --> 17:51.330
<i> YOU</i> NEED TO CARRY THE BURDEN
OF WHAT YOU DID TO ME,

17:51.330 --> 17:52.860
NOT<i> ME.</i>

17:52.860 --> 17:54.790
WELL, NOW YOU
THE BIG SUCCESS.

17:54.800 --> 17:59.230
YOU GOT YOUR OWN HOUSE,
YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

17:59.230 --> 18:02.530
BUT YOU HERE
RUNNING BACK TO ME...

18:02.530 --> 18:05.290
JUST LIKE WHEN I MET YOU.

18:05.300 --> 18:07.490
YOU JUST CAN'T LET ME GO.

18:09.460 --> 18:13.790
I AM HOLDING YOU ACCOUNTABLE
FOR THE PLA--

18:13.800 --> 18:16.430
P-PAIN YOU INFLICTED
ON ME.

18:16.430 --> 18:20.260
YOU AIN'T HOLDING ME
ACCOUNTABLE FOR A DAMN THING.

18:20.260 --> 18:22.160
SHOOT,
I'M THE VICTIM HERE.

18:22.160 --> 18:24.590
AFTER YOUR HOT HEAD
ATTACKED ME, SHOOT,

18:24.600 --> 18:26.330
I MIGHT COULD
PRESS CHARGES!

18:26.330 --> 18:29.260
AUNT VI, LET'S GO.

18:29.260 --> 18:31.530
HE'S GOT NOTHING
TO OFFER YOU.

18:31.530 --> 18:35.690
BETTER LISTEN TO HER.
YOU NEVER DID HAVE NO SENSE.

18:35.700 --> 18:44.630
♪♪

18:50.530 --> 18:52.060
[ SCREAMS ]

19:01.030 --> 19:02.930
NICE HOUSE, JIMMY.

19:07.330 --> 19:10.590
I SEE.

19:10.600 --> 19:15.530
YOU THE ONE THAT HAD TO
CLEAN UP TO COME SEE ME,

19:15.530 --> 19:18.890
'CAUSE YOU<i> KNOW</i>
YOU AIN'T NOTHING.

19:18.900 --> 19:21.360
NEVER BEEN NOTHING.

19:21.360 --> 19:24.560
THIS YOUR LIFE.

19:24.560 --> 19:27.490
YOUR PRIME OVER.

19:27.500 --> 19:31.930
ALL YOU GOT
IS NASTY WORDS.

19:31.930 --> 19:41.390
♪♪

19:41.400 --> 19:43.790
<i> I</i> WON.

19:43.800 --> 19:46.130
I GOT THE GOOD LIFE.

19:46.130 --> 19:48.930
I GOT THE MONEY.

19:48.930 --> 19:50.930
I GOT THE HOUSE.

19:50.930 --> 19:53.790
[ LAUGHS ]

19:53.800 --> 19:56.730
I GOT THE BUSINESS.
I GOT THE RESPECT.

19:56.730 --> 20:01.660
♪♪

20:01.660 --> 20:03.430
LOVE.

20:05.600 --> 20:09.530
AND YOU GOT NOTHIN'.

20:09.530 --> 20:14.990
YOU'RE JUST AN OLD,
WORN-DOWN DOG.

20:15.000 --> 20:16.960
YOU AIN'T SHIT.

20:18.730 --> 20:20.790
NEVER HAVE BEEN.

20:22.700 --> 20:25.260
[ SIGHS ]

20:25.260 --> 20:29.060
♪♪

20:29.060 --> 20:32.590
[ LAUGHS ]

20:32.600 --> 20:34.630
COME ON, BABY.

20:42.400 --> 20:45.430
I'M SORRY, JIMMY. I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WAS HAVING COMPANY.

20:45.430 --> 20:46.630
THERE WAS A LINE
AT THE STORE,

20:46.630 --> 20:48.630
BUT I CAN GET DINNER
GOING RIGHT AWAY.

20:48.630 --> 20:50.760
GO ON IN THE HOUSE,
LAYLA.

20:50.760 --> 20:52.490
NO!

20:56.430 --> 20:59.660
HE GIVE YOU THAT?
WHAT WAS THE REASON?

20:59.660 --> 21:01.890
THE SOUP TOO HOT?

21:01.900 --> 21:05.860
YOU DIDN'T MAKE THE BED CRISP
LIKE HE LIKE IT?

21:05.860 --> 21:10.360
LAYLA!
COME IN THIS HOUSE!

21:10.360 --> 21:13.460
I KNOW YOU FEEL LIKE
YOU AIN'T GOT CHOICES,

21:13.460 --> 21:14.930
BUT YOU DO.

21:14.930 --> 21:17.730
LAYLA!
DON'T YOU TALK TO HER.

21:17.730 --> 21:19.330
SHE DON'T MEAN YOU
NO GOOD!

21:19.330 --> 21:22.790
THIS IS GROWN-FOLK TALK,
JIMMY DALE,

21:22.800 --> 21:26.530
WHICH MEANS THAT AIN'T GOT
A DAMN THING TO DO WITH YOU.

21:26.530 --> 21:27.860
AIN'T GOT --
WHAT THE HELL?

21:27.860 --> 21:31.160
DON'T YOU TAKE
NOT ONE MORE STEP.

21:34.060 --> 21:37.130
YOU DON'T KNOW ME,
BUT I'M YOU --

21:37.130 --> 21:38.530
30 YEARS AGO.

21:38.530 --> 21:42.530
SAME SCARED LOOK,
SAME HITTIN' BRUISES.

21:42.530 --> 21:45.330
I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE
GOING THROUGH.

21:45.330 --> 21:49.060
BELIEVE ME. YOU DON'T
HAVE TO STAY HERE.

21:50.860 --> 21:52.730
BUT I DON'T HAVE
NOWHERE TO GO.

21:52.730 --> 21:54.260
I KNOW A PLACE.

21:54.260 --> 21:56.730
I CAN TAKE YOU THERE
RIGHT NOW.

21:56.730 --> 21:59.990
THERE'S A BETTER LIFE
WAITING FOR YOU.

22:00.000 --> 22:02.590
ALL YOU GOT TO DO
IS TAKE ONE STEP.

22:02.600 --> 22:04.630
♪♪

22:04.630 --> 22:05.990
WHAT IF HE'D FIND ME?

22:06.000 --> 22:09.460
THEN HE'LL FIND<i> ME,</i> TOO.

22:09.460 --> 22:12.490
COME ON, BABY.

22:12.500 --> 22:15.790
DROP THAT BAG
AND COME WITH ME.

22:15.800 --> 22:17.460
-LAYLA?
-DON'T LOOK BACK.

22:17.460 --> 22:18.930
-YOU COME BACK HERE.
-DON'T LOOK BACK.

22:18.930 --> 22:21.990
LAYLA, COME BACK HERE
RIGHT NOW!

22:22.000 --> 22:24.830
VIOLET!
THIS AIN'T OVER!

22:24.830 --> 22:27.360
THIS AIN'T OVER BY A LONG SHOT!

22:27.360 --> 22:29.560
YOU AIN'T HEARD THE LAST OF ME!

22:29.560 --> 22:32.460
THIS AIN'T THE LAST
YOU GONNA HEAR OF ME!

22:32.460 --> 22:34.890
[ VEHICLE DEPARTS ]

22:42.300 --> 22:44.160
[ LAUGHTER ]

22:44.160 --> 22:45.960
-I MAKE YOU LAUGH, THOUGH.
-SOMETIMES.

22:45.960 --> 22:47.960
-[ GASPS ] SOMETIMES?
-LOOK AT THIS ONE.

22:47.960 --> 22:49.990
-LOOK LIKE YOU.
-AWW. BEAUTIFUL.

22:50.000 --> 22:52.190
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

22:52.200 --> 22:53.660
-BABE.
-YES.

22:53.660 --> 22:56.260
-YOU SEE THIS?
-WHAT'S THIS?

22:56.260 --> 22:58.590
DURING, UH, KATRINA,
THE PHOTOGRAPHER'S FILM

22:58.600 --> 23:00.790
WAS LEFT BEHIND,
AND IT ALL GOT WATERLOGGED.

23:00.800 --> 23:02.430
-MM-HMM.
-SO THEY WERE GONNA TOSS IT,

23:02.430 --> 23:03.830
BUT INSTEAD
THEY LET IT DRY OUT.

23:03.830 --> 23:07.730
AND IT TURNED INTO THESE IMAGES,
WARPED AND RUINED...

23:07.730 --> 23:12.590
BUT STUNNING IN
A TOTALLY UNEXPECTED WAY.

23:12.600 --> 23:16.330
-BEAUTY OUT OF DESTRUCTION.
-YEAH.

23:16.330 --> 23:19.060
I LIKE WHEN YOU TALK
ABOUT PHOTOGRAPHY.

23:19.060 --> 23:21.390
HOPE YOU DON'T DROP IT
WHEN YOU GO TO<i> HARVARD.</i>

23:21.400 --> 23:24.330
YEAH.
I DON'T KNOW.

23:24.330 --> 23:29.060
PHOTOGRAPHY IS MORE THAN
JUST A HOBBY FOR ME.

23:29.060 --> 23:30.630
I'M NOT GONNA GIVE IT UP.

23:33.230 --> 23:37.660
I MEAN, OF COURSE, I WON'T BE
AS FULL-TIME AS YOU,

23:37.660 --> 23:40.330
MISS FOUR-YEAR
FULL ART SCHOLARSHIP.

23:40.330 --> 23:43.860
-OKAY.
-THANK YOU.

23:43.860 --> 23:45.330
SENT MY ACCEPTANCE IN
YESTERDAY.

23:45.330 --> 23:46.530
-OH, YEAH?
-YES.

23:46.530 --> 23:47.930
MAMA...WAS ON MY SHOULDER
THE WHOLE TIME.

23:47.930 --> 23:51.330
YEAH. MY MOM'S BEEN
DOING THE MOST, TOO.

23:51.330 --> 23:53.390
[ SIGHS ]

23:56.800 --> 23:58.930
IT'S STARTING TO FEEL REAL.

23:58.930 --> 24:01.130
♪♪

24:01.130 --> 24:02.930
YEAH.

24:05.030 --> 24:08.460
THIS TIME NEXT YEAR,
WE'LL BE MILES APART.

24:08.460 --> 24:10.730
BUT WE SURVIVED
THE SUMMER APART.

24:10.730 --> 24:14.260
AND YOU'LL BE BACK FOR
THE HOLIDAYS AND SUMMERS.

24:14.260 --> 24:16.330
-MM-HMM.
-WE'LL BE FINE.

24:16.330 --> 24:19.660
♪♪

24:19.660 --> 24:23.390
I FEEL LIKE PEOPLE SAY THAT,
BUT THEN THEY...BREAK UP.

24:23.400 --> 24:30.130
♪♪

24:30.130 --> 24:32.330
COME HERE.

24:32.330 --> 24:40.130
♪♪

24:40.130 --> 24:43.530
I LOVE YOU.

24:43.530 --> 24:45.730
YOU KNOW THAT, RIGHT?

24:45.730 --> 24:48.260
♪♪

24:48.260 --> 24:51.260
AND NO MATTER HOW FAR
AWAY I GO, I'M WITH YOU.

24:51.260 --> 24:56.360
♪♪

24:56.360 --> 24:58.630
AND I'M WITH<i> YOU.</i>

24:58.630 --> 25:06.730
♪♪

25:06.730 --> 25:10.260
THIS IS THE LOUISIANA HOME FOR
DOMESTIC ABUSE SURVIVORS --

25:10.260 --> 25:11.960
WOMEN JUST LIKE US.

25:11.960 --> 25:13.130
IT'S SAFE, SECURE.

25:13.130 --> 25:16.060
AND WHEN YOU'RE READY,

25:16.060 --> 25:20.390
THERE'S A JOB WAITING FOR YOU
AT VI'S PRIZE PIES.

25:20.400 --> 25:25.190
AGAIN, IF YOU NEED
ANYTHING, YOU CALL ME.

25:25.200 --> 25:26.990
YOU HAVE MY NUMBER.

25:27.000 --> 25:29.130
-OKAY.
-YOU READY?

25:29.130 --> 25:31.290
♪♪

25:31.300 --> 25:33.030
ALRIGHT, BABY.

25:33.030 --> 25:34.690
COME ON.

25:34.700 --> 25:36.890
[ SIGHS ] OKAY.

25:36.900 --> 25:41.560
SO, JOANNE, IF SHE TRIES TO GO
BACK, YOU CALL ME RIGHT AWAY.

25:41.560 --> 25:43.830
-OKAY.
-THANK YOU, BABY.

25:43.830 --> 25:46.830
♪♪

25:46.830 --> 25:50.290
COME ON. WE GOT A LOT MORE
DRIVING TO DO.

25:55.800 --> 25:57.860
THIS IS PERFECT.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

25:57.860 --> 26:02.130
♪♪

26:02.130 --> 26:03.860
HI, MISS VIOLET.

26:03.860 --> 26:06.660
♪♪

26:06.660 --> 26:09.330
HEY, BABY.
HOW YOU DOING?

26:09.330 --> 26:11.930
MUCH BETTER.

26:11.930 --> 26:14.090
GLAD TO HEAR IT.

26:14.100 --> 26:16.160
THANK YOU.

26:16.160 --> 26:17.960
YOU DON'T NEED
TO THANK ME.

26:17.960 --> 26:19.760
YES, I DO.

26:19.760 --> 26:21.960
YOU HELPED ME...

26:21.960 --> 26:25.460
WHEN I WAS AT MY LOWEST.

26:25.460 --> 26:28.260
AND YOU DIDN'T HAVE TO.

26:28.260 --> 26:30.630
YOU TOOK A CHANCE
ON HELPING ME.

26:30.630 --> 26:33.290
♪♪

26:33.300 --> 26:35.430
LISTEN.

26:35.430 --> 26:39.060
I KNOW THAT WE DON'T ALWAYS
SEE THINGS THE SAME,

26:39.060 --> 26:42.660
BUT I JUST DON'T FEEL YOU NEED
TO CARRY AROUND SHAME

26:42.660 --> 26:44.630
THAT AIN'T YOURS.

26:44.630 --> 26:47.160
♪♪

26:47.160 --> 26:50.660
WE ALL DESERVE A SECOND CHANCE
TO GET THINGS RIGHT.

26:50.660 --> 26:58.460
♪♪

26:58.460 --> 27:01.390
THIS IS MY ONE-MONTH CHIP.

27:01.400 --> 27:03.360
♪♪

27:03.360 --> 27:05.960
I USED TO HAVE
A WHOLE PILE LIKE THIS.

27:05.960 --> 27:07.560
♪♪

27:07.560 --> 27:09.430
NOW IT'S, UM...

27:09.430 --> 27:14.260
PROBABLY MY MOST VALUED
POSSESSION...

27:14.260 --> 27:17.390
AFTER BLUE.

27:17.400 --> 27:19.460
I'D LIKE YOU TO HAVE IT.

27:19.460 --> 27:26.860
♪♪

27:26.860 --> 27:34.260
♪♪

27:34.260 --> 27:37.660
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

27:37.660 --> 27:39.860
CAN I HAVE EVERYONE'S ATTENTION?

27:39.860 --> 27:41.760
[ CONVERSATIONS STOP ]

27:43.900 --> 27:47.130
I WANNA THANK ALL OF YOU
FOR YOUR HARD WORK.

27:47.130 --> 27:51.960
WE'RE NEAR THE END,
AND YOU'VE GIVEN YOUR ALL.

27:51.960 --> 27:54.330
IN FACT, WE'VE DONE SO WELL

27:54.330 --> 27:58.130
THAT THE PEOPLE BACKING
THE BOUDREAUX CAMPAIGN

27:58.130 --> 28:02.660
ARE PULLING EVERY DIRTY TRICK
IN THE BOOK TO STEAL THIS RACE.

28:02.660 --> 28:06.590
WE'VE, UH, HAD OUR VOTERS
PURGED FROM THE ROLLS.

28:06.600 --> 28:09.190
AND NOW, THEY'VE RELOCATED
THE POLLING PLACE

28:09.200 --> 28:15.030
FOR MOST OF OUR LATINX VOTERS
TO, UH, A SPOT OUTSIDE OF TOWN.

28:15.030 --> 28:17.690
IF WE ARE NOT ABLE TO GET
THESE VOTERS TO THE POLLS

28:17.700 --> 28:21.830
IN LARGE ENOUGH NUMBERS...

28:21.830 --> 28:23.960
WE WILL PROBABLY LOSE.

28:23.960 --> 28:27.590
NOW, I CAN HANDLE LOSING A RACE
FAIR AND SQUARE.

28:27.600 --> 28:32.560
BUT THIS ISN'T THAT.

28:32.560 --> 28:36.360
AND IT ALSO
AIN'T NOTHING NEW.

28:36.360 --> 28:39.590
JUST A NEW TWIST
ON AN OLD TRICK.

28:39.600 --> 28:43.660
NOW, IF IT'S A MATTER OF
GETTING SOULS TO THE POLLS,

28:43.660 --> 28:45.790
WE'LL DO IT
THE OLD-FASHIONED WAY.

28:45.800 --> 28:48.060
WE PUT TOGETHER
A PHONE TREE,

28:48.060 --> 28:50.060
GET THE WORD OUT
TO EVERYBODY WE KNOW.

28:50.060 --> 28:52.060
AND I'VE ALREADY TALKED
TO PASTOR MARTINEZ

28:52.060 --> 28:53.790
ABOUT GETTING
SOME OF HIS MEMBERS

28:53.800 --> 28:56.190
TO PUT TOGETHER
A TRANSPORTATION SCHEDULE.

28:56.200 --> 28:58.330
NOW, WE CAN ARRANGE
PICK-UP TIMES

28:58.330 --> 29:01.860
AND LOCATIONS
TO MAXIMIZE THE TURNOUT.

29:01.860 --> 29:04.390
WE'RE NOT GOING TO
JUST LAY DOWN AND DIE.

29:04.400 --> 29:06.530
-NO!
-THAT'S RIGHT!

29:06.530 --> 29:08.590
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

29:08.600 --> 29:12.590
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

29:12.600 --> 29:15.830
WE'RE GONNA DO
WHATEVER WE HAVE TO.

29:15.830 --> 29:17.460
OKAY?

29:23.330 --> 29:25.530
THANK YOU.

29:25.530 --> 29:27.060
THANK YOU.

29:30.730 --> 29:32.660
[ SIGHS ]

29:34.360 --> 29:36.090
YOU KNOW...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

29:36.100 --> 29:39.090
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
IN YEARS

29:39.100 --> 29:42.830
THAT I HAVEN'T BEEN
THINKING ABOUT THAT BOX.

29:47.730 --> 29:49.990
I THOUGHT THAT, WELL,

29:50.000 --> 29:54.190
IF HE TOOK BACK
THOSE BAD MEMORIES,

29:54.200 --> 29:59.060
THEN I'D BE FREE OF EVERYTHING
THAT HE BROUGHT BACK UP IN ME.

29:59.060 --> 30:01.660
BUT NOW I SEE...

30:01.660 --> 30:05.590
THAT IT AIN'T ABOUT
LOOKING BACK.

30:05.600 --> 30:06.990
IT NEVER IS.

30:07.000 --> 30:10.730
IT'S ABOUT
THE HERE AND NOW.

30:10.730 --> 30:14.490
BREAKING BAD CYCLES.

30:18.060 --> 30:19.860
AND LOOKING FORWARD.

30:22.200 --> 30:24.530
NO MORE SECRETS.

30:24.530 --> 30:27.260
♪♪

30:27.260 --> 30:29.330
YOU DID GOOD, AUNT VI.

30:29.330 --> 30:32.060
♪♪

30:32.060 --> 30:34.260
[ LAUGHS ]

30:34.260 --> 30:38.790
♪♪

30:38.800 --> 30:40.860
I'M GLAD YOU WERE WITH ME.

30:40.860 --> 30:44.760
♪♪

30:44.760 --> 30:49.730
YOU, UM, YOU WANT SOME PIE
TO GO WITH THAT?

30:49.730 --> 30:52.090
I'LL GO CUT YOU A PIECE.

30:52.100 --> 30:56.730
♪♪

30:56.730 --> 30:59.330
MY SOURCES AND I LOOKED
INTO OLD WORLD ENERGY.

30:59.330 --> 31:02.660
AND THEY TEND TO
RIDE INTO SMALL TOWNS

31:02.660 --> 31:04.990
AND RUN ROUGHSHOD OVER THEM
TO GET WHAT THEY WANT,

31:05.000 --> 31:06.530
NO MATTER WHAT THE COST
TO THE TOWN.

31:06.530 --> 31:07.960
YEAH, NO SURPRISE THERE.

31:07.960 --> 31:09.630
BUT WHAT<i> IS</i> SURPRISING --

31:09.630 --> 31:11.830
THAT CONSULTANT WE THOUGHT
WAS GONNA BE THE MISSING LINK,

31:11.830 --> 31:14.790
HANK MILLER, HE DOESN'T WORK
FOR OLD WORLD ENERGY.

31:14.800 --> 31:16.330
WHO<i> DOES</i> HE WORK FOR?

31:16.330 --> 31:18.860
STILL NOT CLEAR.

31:18.860 --> 31:20.860
BUT I WENT BY ONE OF OLD WORLD
ENERGY'S HEADQUARTERS

31:20.860 --> 31:22.190
THIS AFTERNOON.

31:22.200 --> 31:24.790
IT'S JUST A TINY OFFICE
WITH A RECEPTIONIST.

31:24.800 --> 31:26.030
A SHELL COMPANY.

31:26.030 --> 31:28.160
AND INSIDE THAT SHELL
IS A HOLDING COMPANY

31:28.160 --> 31:30.130
CALLED
THE BECKINGTON GROUP.

31:30.130 --> 31:32.530
MOST OF THEIR INFORMATION
IS HIDDEN BEHIND A TRUST,

31:32.530 --> 31:34.490
BUT I DID FIND A NAME
ON A DOCUMENT

31:34.500 --> 31:37.390
CHALLENGING VOTER REGISTRATIONS
IN SAINT JO --

31:37.400 --> 31:39.260
SOME GUY NAMED
PARKER CAMPBELL.

31:39.260 --> 31:41.330
WELL, IT'S MORE
THAN A CHALLENGE NOW.

31:41.330 --> 31:42.930
PROSPER JUST
FOUND OUT THAT HE,

31:42.930 --> 31:45.990
ALONG WITH HUNDREDS OF
OTHER BLACK AND BROWN VOTERS,

31:46.000 --> 31:48.130
HAVE BEEN PURGED
FROM THE VOTER ROLLS.

31:48.130 --> 31:49.190
-WHAT?
-MM-HMM.

31:49.200 --> 31:51.030
WE ALSO DISCOVERED
THAT THE POLLING STATION

31:51.030 --> 31:53.160
FOR PASTOR MARTINEZ'S
DISTRICT

31:53.160 --> 31:55.660
WAS RELOCATED OVER 10 MILES
AWAY AT THE LAST MINUTE.

31:55.660 --> 31:57.130
A WEEK
BEFORE THE ELECTION?!

31:57.130 --> 31:59.130
I'VE GOT MY LAWYERS
WORKING ON IT ALREADY.

31:59.130 --> 32:02.060
BUT THIS...

32:02.060 --> 32:06.260
THIS FEELS BIGGER
THAN THE LANDRY FAMILY.

32:06.260 --> 32:09.860
IF THIS PARKER CAMPBELL
AND THE BECKINGTON GROUP

32:09.860 --> 32:13.330
ARE SO POWERFUL THEY CAN
HIDE THEIR EXISTENCE,

32:13.330 --> 32:16.590
WHAT ELSE
ARE THEY CAPABLE OF?

32:16.600 --> 32:19.130
WHO ARE THESE PEOPLE?

32:19.130 --> 32:22.190
I HAVE NO IDEA.

32:22.200 --> 32:26.190
BUT I PROMISE YOU,
WE'LL GET TO THE BOTTOM OF IT.

32:26.200 --> 32:30.460
UNTIL THEN, WE CAN TRY TO
ENJOY MICAH'S CELEBRATION.

32:30.460 --> 32:32.330
ALRIGHT?

32:32.330 --> 32:39.790
♪♪

32:43.030 --> 32:44.760
♪♪

32:44.760 --> 32:45.960
SIT RIGHT HERE, BLUE.

32:45.960 --> 32:48.290
I'VE ALREADY PICKED
A SEAT, POPS.

32:49.930 --> 32:52.930
-[ LAUGHS ] BLUE.
-HMM?

32:52.930 --> 32:55.330
MAYBE YOU SHOULD GO BACK
AND SIT WITH YOUR DAD.

32:55.330 --> 32:57.460
♪♪

32:57.460 --> 33:00.790
I WANNA S-SIT WITH YOU.

33:00.800 --> 33:02.590
COME ON. LET'S GO
TO THE BATHROOM, BLUE.

33:02.600 --> 33:05.660
WASH YOUR HANDS.
COME ON.

33:05.660 --> 33:09.330
RALPH ANGEL, DON'T PUT THAT BOY
IN THE MIDDLE OF THIS MESS.

33:09.330 --> 33:11.730
♪♪

33:11.730 --> 33:15.730
JUST 'CAUSE YOU IN NOVA CORNER,
THAT MEAN WE ALL GOTTA BE?

33:15.730 --> 33:17.460
HUH?

33:17.460 --> 33:19.930
♪♪

33:19.930 --> 33:21.890
[ KNOCK ON DOOR,
WATER RUNNING ]

33:21.900 --> 33:24.990
-LITTLE MAN. YOU GOOD?
-YEAH.

33:28.330 --> 33:30.060
[ WATER STOPS ]

33:32.460 --> 33:36.530
POP, WHY ARE YOU MAD
AT AUNTIE NOVA?

33:36.530 --> 33:38.430
WHO SAID I WAS MAD AT HER?

33:38.430 --> 33:42.030
I HEARD YOU THIS MORNING.
YOU SOUNDED UPSET.

33:45.400 --> 33:48.260
YEAH, WELL,
YOUR AUNTIE NOVA

33:48.260 --> 33:50.730
DID SOMETHING
SHE SHOULDN'T HAVE.

33:50.730 --> 33:52.530
WELL, DID SHE SAY SORRY?

33:52.530 --> 33:55.890
NO. NOT REALLY.

33:57.730 --> 33:59.530
SORT OF.

33:59.530 --> 34:01.530
SHE THINK
SHE IN THE RIGHT.

34:01.530 --> 34:04.760
I DISAGREE.

34:04.760 --> 34:06.830
IT'S JUST LIKE WHEN MARCUS SAID
IT WAS HIS TURN

34:06.830 --> 34:10.490
TO PLAY MINECRAFT,
BUT IT WAS ACTUALLY MINE.

34:10.500 --> 34:12.560
WE HAD A BIG FIGHT
ABOUT IT.

34:14.130 --> 34:16.930
SO, HOW'D YOU AND MARCUS
WORK THIS OUT?

34:16.930 --> 34:20.730
WELL, WE DECIDED
TO EACH TAKE TWO TURNS.

34:20.730 --> 34:23.190
BECAUSE MARCUS' MOM SAID,

34:23.200 --> 34:26.530
IT'S NOT WORTH NOT BEING
FRIENDS OVER THE GAME,

34:26.530 --> 34:29.930
THAT WE HAVE MORE IN COMMON
THAN WE HAVE DIFFERENT.

34:29.930 --> 34:32.730
♪♪

34:32.730 --> 34:34.860
SO YOU'RE
A BIG BOY NOW, HUH?

34:34.860 --> 34:37.460
-[ CHUCKLES ]
-SMART, TOO, HUH?

34:37.460 --> 34:40.790
-COME HERE.
-DAD, I LOVE YOU.

34:40.800 --> 34:43.530
-LOVE YOU MORE.
-I LOVE YOU EVEN MORE.

34:43.530 --> 34:46.730
-SAY, LISTEN.
-WHAT?

34:46.730 --> 34:50.690
GO SIT WITH YOUR AUNTIE NOVA
IF YOU WANT TO.

34:50.700 --> 34:52.030
I AM.

34:52.030 --> 34:54.130
-ALRIGHT.
-BYE.

34:54.130 --> 35:00.590
♪♪

35:00.600 --> 35:04.190
I'D JUST LIKE TO SAY
A FEW WORDS.

35:04.200 --> 35:06.060
FEW WORDS?
COME ON, CHARLEY.

35:06.060 --> 35:08.730
YOU BEEN WAITING ON THIS
YOUR WHOLE LIFE.

35:08.730 --> 35:10.590
[ LAUGHTER ]
COME ON.

35:10.600 --> 35:12.260
YES, I HAVE.

35:12.260 --> 35:14.860
[ LAUGHTER ]

35:14.860 --> 35:18.330
MICAH, YOU HAVE PUT IN THE WORK

35:18.330 --> 35:21.390
TO MAKE YOURSELF STAND OUT.

35:21.400 --> 35:25.930
SO HERE YOU ARE,
OFF TO HARVARD.

35:25.930 --> 35:28.490
AND I AM SO, SO PROUD.

35:28.500 --> 35:32.260
♪♪

35:32.260 --> 35:34.390
-WHAT'S THIS?
-A LITTLE SOMETHING.

35:34.400 --> 35:38.590
[ LAUGHS ]
THANK YOU.

35:38.600 --> 35:40.660
GO ON. SEE WHAT YOU GOT.

35:40.660 --> 35:43.560
♪♪

35:43.560 --> 35:45.560
LET'S SEE WHAT YOU GOT.

35:45.560 --> 35:47.230
OKAY.

35:47.230 --> 35:50.690
♪♪

35:50.700 --> 35:52.760
OH. THE ROLEX, THOUGH.

35:52.760 --> 35:54.190
[ LAUGHTER ]

35:54.200 --> 35:55.930
FANCY!

35:55.930 --> 35:58.090
Ralph Angel: FANCY...

35:58.100 --> 36:00.090
STARTING YOUR COLLEGE LIFE
RIGHT, RIGHT?

36:00.100 --> 36:04.060
-WOW. YEAH.
-YEAH!

36:04.060 --> 36:07.460
"MICAH, GO CONFIDENTLY IN
THE DIRECTION OF YOUR DREAMS.

36:07.460 --> 36:10.730
LOVE, MOM AND DAD."

36:10.730 --> 36:13.460
THANK YOU, MA.
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

36:13.460 --> 36:16.990
SO, HERE IS TO MICAH WEST.

36:17.000 --> 36:18.330
[ Laughter ]

36:18.330 --> 36:20.630
-BELOVED SON.
-AND NEPHEW!

36:20.630 --> 36:22.790
YEAH.

36:22.800 --> 36:25.490
YOU HAVE SO MUCH
TO GIVE THE WORLD.

36:25.500 --> 36:26.690
CONGRATS, BABY.

36:26.700 --> 36:28.160
-HEAR, HEAR.
-HEAR, HEAR.

36:28.160 --> 36:30.030
-TO MICAH.
-CHEERS.

36:30.030 --> 36:31.460
All: CHEERS.

36:31.460 --> 36:33.430
[ LAUGHS ]

36:33.430 --> 36:36.930
♪♪

36:36.930 --> 36:39.590
MOM.

36:39.600 --> 36:43.530
I WAS GONNA WAIT UNTIL
AFTER THE ELECTION, BUT...

36:43.530 --> 36:46.060
♪♪

36:46.060 --> 36:47.830
RADICAL TRUTH, RIGHT?

36:47.830 --> 36:50.030
♪♪

36:50.030 --> 36:52.430
UH, WHAT'S GOING ON, MICAH?

36:52.430 --> 36:54.890
MOM, I'M NOT
GOING TO HARVARD.

36:54.900 --> 36:56.430
I'M GOING TO --
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

36:56.430 --> 37:00.190
I'M GOING TO XAVIER UNIVERSITY
HERE IN NOLA.

37:00.200 --> 37:02.660
WAIT. WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

37:02.660 --> 37:04.590
XAVIER'S NOT EVEN
ON OUR -- OUR LIST.

37:04.600 --> 37:06.830
I-I MADE MY OWN LIST.

37:06.830 --> 37:10.890
I'M GONNA STUDY ART
AND POLITICAL SCIENCE

37:10.900 --> 37:13.430
AND PURSUE A CAREER
IN PHOTOGRAPHY.

37:13.430 --> 37:19.330
♪♪

37:19.330 --> 37:22.290
-YOU KNEW ABOUT THIS?
-NO.

37:22.300 --> 37:25.960
BUT GOOD FOR YOU, MICAH.
IT'S A FINE CHOICE.

37:25.960 --> 37:34.360
♪♪

37:34.360 --> 37:36.090
THIS IS MY FIRST TIME
HEARING ABOUT IT.

37:36.100 --> 37:38.860
NO, I -- I DIDN'T DECIDE
THIS BECAUSE OF KEKE.

37:38.860 --> 37:42.260
MOM, IF ANYTHING,
I DID IT BECAUSE OF<i> YOU.</i>

37:42.260 --> 37:45.860
WATCHING YOU THESE PAST
FEW MONTHS BRIDGING COMMUNITIES

37:45.860 --> 37:49.730
AND FIGHTING FOR WHAT'S RIGHT --
THAT'S WHAT I WANNA DO.

37:49.730 --> 37:51.260
THAT'S WHAT I WANT
MY WORK TO BE ABOUT.

37:51.260 --> 37:54.190
GREAT, GREAT --
GO TO HARVARD,

37:54.200 --> 37:56.590
GET YOUR DEGREE,
AND START A BUSINESS

37:56.600 --> 37:59.090
THAT PUTS JOBS INTO THE HANDS
OF OUR PEOPLE,

37:59.100 --> 38:01.730
WHICH IS WHAT THEY NEED --
NOT MORE PRETTY PICTURES!

38:01.730 --> 38:04.330
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
HEAR HIM OUT.

38:06.200 --> 38:10.130
I-I'VE SPOKEN TO MEN
LIKE MR. PROSPER

38:10.130 --> 38:15.790
AND -- AND UNCLE RA
AND HOLLYWOOD, MR. ROMERO.

38:15.800 --> 38:18.530
I'VE REALIZED THAT
THESE PEOPLE, THIS COMMUNITY

38:18.530 --> 38:20.130
IS WHAT I WANT MY WORK
TO BE ABOUT.

38:20.130 --> 38:22.590
YOU DON'T HAVE TO LIVE IN
THE COMMUNITY TO SUPPORT IT.

38:22.600 --> 38:26.530
-BUT IT HELPS.
-YEAH, AND I WANT TO BE<i> HERE.</i>

38:26.530 --> 38:30.330
HARVARD JUST FEELS
LIKE A POINTLESS DETOUR

38:30.330 --> 38:31.860
FROM WHO I INTEND TO BE.

38:31.860 --> 38:34.060
POINTLESS?!

38:34.060 --> 38:36.530
YOU HAVE BEEN DEALT
A WINNING HAND,

38:36.530 --> 38:39.260
A TOOL TO FIGHT
AGAINST THE PRIVILEGES

38:39.260 --> 38:42.060
THAT THE WORLD WON'T EVER
HAND YOU EASILY!

38:42.060 --> 38:43.590
AND YOU JUST
WANNA TOSS IT AWAY?!

38:43.600 --> 38:44.860
I'M NOT TOSSING IT AWAY.

38:44.860 --> 38:46.630
THERE HAVE BEEN PLENTY
OF SUCCESSFUL MEN AND WOMEN

38:46.630 --> 38:48.530
WHO HAVE GRADUATED
FROM HBCUs!

38:48.530 --> 38:51.560
YES, XAVIER WILL PROVIDE
AN EXCELLENT EDUCATION.

38:51.560 --> 38:53.490
BUT, FRANKLY, COLLEGE
ISN'T ABOUT EDUCATION.

38:53.500 --> 38:55.830
NOT ANYMORE.
-THEN WHAT'S IT ABOUT?

38:55.830 --> 38:57.690
CONNECTIONS.
IN THE REAL WORLD.

38:57.700 --> 39:00.060
THE KIND THE LANDRYS
WIELD EVERY DAY

39:00.060 --> 39:02.860
WITHOUT EVEN
A SECOND THOUGHT.

39:02.860 --> 39:05.990
IT WILL ALLOW EMPLOYERS
TO SEE YOU

39:06.000 --> 39:09.490
AS THE BRIGHT, SENSITIVE
YOUNG MAN THAT YOU ARE.

39:09.500 --> 39:12.030
BABY, IF YOU DO THIS --
I ALREADY DID IT.

39:13.960 --> 39:15.760
I ALREADY DID IT.

39:15.760 --> 39:18.990
I RESCINDED MY ACCEPTANCE LETTER
TO HARVARD THIS MORNING, SO...

39:19.000 --> 39:27.060
♪♪

39:27.060 --> 39:28.790
OKAY.
WELL, WHAT'S DONE IS DONE.

39:28.800 --> 39:31.530
THERE'S NO POINT
ARGUING ABOUT IT.

39:31.530 --> 39:36.530
I PERSONALLY LOVE THE IDEA
OF HAVING YOU CLOSE BY, MICAH.

39:36.530 --> 39:43.260
♪♪

39:43.260 --> 39:50.090
♪♪

39:50.100 --> 39:53.630
I HAVE BEEN IN THE FIGHT
OF MY LIFE

39:53.630 --> 39:57.360
IN WHAT SHOULDN'T
EVEN BE A CONTEST,

39:57.360 --> 39:59.760
ALL BECAUSE THIS COUNTRY
IS SET UP

39:59.760 --> 40:03.030
TO BENEFIT PEOPLE
LIKE THE BOUDREAUXS.

40:03.030 --> 40:05.890
AND NOW YOU'RE
BEING OFFERED A TOOL

40:05.900 --> 40:10.460
TO HELP LEVEL THE FIELD
FOR ALL OF US.

40:10.460 --> 40:13.030
AND YOU DECIDE...

40:13.030 --> 40:15.160
TO JUST THROW IT AWAY?!

40:17.230 --> 40:19.890
HOW DARE YOU, MICAH.

